Youths and Children Visit Mangyongdae 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- Youths and children across the country Sunday made a study tour of the old home of President Kim Il Sung in Mangyongdae on the occasion of the Day of the Sun (his birth anniversary), the greatest holiday of the nation.
 Participating in the study tour were officials of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League and over 4,000 working youths and school youth and children from different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to their study tour they climbed Mansu Hill to lay floral baskets and bouquets before the statue of Kim Il Sung and make a bow in humble reverence.
 Then they began their study tour of the old home in Mangyongdae, carrying flags bearing the portraits of Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il in the van.
 They vigorously marched streets of the capital, fluttering flags of the Workers' Party of Korea, the DPRK and the youth league and red flags. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citizens and school youth and children in the capital inspired them, throwing confetti, waving bouquets and enthusiastically cheering along the streets.
 Upon their arrival in Mangyongdae, they firstly laid wreaths and bouquets before the graves of Kim Po Hyon and Ri Po Ik, grandparents of Kim Il Sung, and the graves of his parents Kim Hyong Jik and Kang Pan Sok, and paid silent tributes.
 They visited the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Museum and the old home in time-honored Mangyongdae. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round with deep attention historic relics impregnated with the personal odor of members of the revolutionary family in Mangyongdae and posed for souvenir photographs in front of the old home before inspecting revolutionary relics on Mangyong Hill.

Socialism of Korea Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- Seminars were held in Bangladesh, Democratic Congo and Poland on March 26 and 28 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 The chairman of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Bangladesh and other speakers pointed out that President Kim Il Sung founded the immortal Juche idea and performed great feats for the Korean revolution and the accomplishment of the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has brilliantly carried forward the revolutionary cause of Kim Il Sung and wisely led the drive of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with his Songun politics, they noted, and added: The socialism of Korea is a model of building a new society. It is an important task of the world progressive people to denounce the imperialists for their moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and support the socialism of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea in Democratic Congo in his speech explained the essence and great vitality of the Juche idea and called upon the peoples of all the countries to firmly arm themselves with the Juche idea and apply it thoroughly in order to defend independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-chairman of the National Executive Committee of the Polish Communist Party highly praised Kim Jong Il for smashing the imperialists' ferocious anti-socialist, anti-DPRK moves with his unique Songun politics and demonstrating the invincible might of socialist Korea all over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar held in Bangladesh.

Struggle for Peace against War Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- The United States is getting frantic in its moves to ignite a war against the DPRK in order to stem the trend of the Korean nation's history toward reconciliation and reunification and realize its ambition for domination over the whole of Korea. In order to shatter the vicious moves of the U.S. imperialists for a war of aggression and bring about steady progress of the era of independent reunification, all the Koreans at home and abroad should wage a vigorous struggle under the banner of peace against war.
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. 
 Their ambition to invade the DPRK and dominate the whole of Korea remains unchanged and is becoming all the more pronounced than ever before, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. Korea policy is a hostile policy and a criminal policy for a war of aggression.
 The U.S. imperialists' moves for a war against the DPRK have always been frantic. Their dangerous and brigandish nature has reached the worst phase since Bush came to power. Since the outset of office his bellicose group has systematically escalated its moves against the DPRK, extremely antagonizing it and listing it as a target of preemptive nuclear attack. The U.S is now persisting in its campaign to do harm to the DPRK and pressurize it while barring the six-party talks from resuming. This is, in fact, aimed at inventing a pretext to provoke a war against the DPRK.
 To struggle against the outside forces' moves for aggression and war under the banner of peace against war is a sacred duty of the Korean nation to achieve the independent national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An atmosphere of peace is a prerequisite to independent national reunification.
 Dialogue and war exercises can never go together. If ceaseless joint military exercises with foreign forces are allowed to go on in south Korea against fellow countrymen as now, it is impossible to hold north-south dialogue nor is it possible to expect any desired results from the talks to be held by the north and the south in an atmosphere of mutual distrust and confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the habitual method of the U.S. imperialists to chill the ardent desire of the Korean nation for reunification and obstruct the cause of national reunification through the moves for a war against the DPRK. By escalating such provocative war maneuvers on the Korean Peninsula in particular, they seek to deter the north-south relations from favorably improving and keep the movement for national reunification from making progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should never allow them to go on with their reckless war exercises to invade the DPRK.

Japan's Ambition to Grab Tok Islet Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- The south Korean political circle is rejecting the Japanese government's ambition to grab Tok Islet, according to radio reports from south Korea.
 Ruling and opposition parties including the Uri Party charged that the action taken by the Japanese Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology to allow the description of Tok Islet as part of the Japanese territory in history and geography textbooks for high school students is a serious diplomatic provocation to the Koreans and an encroachment upon their spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade of south Korea in a statement demanded the Japanese government retract its assertion at once, dismissing it unreasonable and intolerable. It declared that south Korea would deal with the issue of Tok Islet in strong terms from the stand of defending the territory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ministry clarified its stand that the Japanese government's behavior is unacceptable, telling the Japanese ambassador in Seoul that the description of Tok Islet in high school textbooks in Japan is a wanton violation of the sovereignty of Korea.
 The south Korean ambassador to Japan also lodged a protest with the Japanese Foreign Ministry against this matter on March 31.

Ri Jong Song Gymnastic Movement Named 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- The International Gymnastics Federation decided to call the gymnastic movement of Ri Jong Song of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea "Ri Jong Song Movement" in December last.
 He, active in the April 25 Sports Group, gave a good account of himself by performing his unique movement in floor exercises in a flawless way at several international gymnastic contests including the Athens Olympic Games and the fourth East Asian Games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He turned double aerial backward tucked with three twists in the floor exercises, drawing attention of gymnastics experts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The movement was marked on the high-degree diagram of international gymnastics technique published by the IGF to be distributed to gymnastics experts of different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Ri Jong Song Movement" has brought the number of the movements of Korean gymnasts registered by the IGF to five in all. The others are "Ri Song Sop Movement" (horizontal bar), "Ri Chol Hun Movement" (pommel), "Pak Kyong Sil Movement" (uneven bars) and "Kim Kwang Suk Movement" (uneven bars).
